Source:
https://github.com/Lahvuun/sekirofpsunlock

download latest release with .tar.gz extension:
https://github.com/Lahvuun/sekirofpsunlock/releases/tag/v0.2.3
Last update was 6 years ago so I dont newer versions.

extract file downloaded .tar.gz:
tar -xzf (YourFileName).tar.gz

Give extracted mod run permissions
chmod +x sekirofpsunlock

Copy both (dxvk.conf and sekirofpsunlock) extracted files into sekiro steam folder, for me it's in:
/home/akash/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/common/Sekiro/

Put launch command is steam Launch options, for me it's (read source repository):
gamescope -W 3440 -H 1440 -r 120 -f --force-grab-cursor -- %command% & ./sekirofpsunlock 30 set-resolution 3440 3440 1440 set-fps 100

